article.headline: Milwaukee 84, Detroit 74
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Paris Gulley scored 26 points, making six 3-pointers, and Milwaukee rolled past Detroit 84-74 Saturday night. James Haarsma added 17 points for the Panthers (13-6, 6-1), who took a half-game lead in the Horizon League standings, pending Cleveland State's game on Sunday at Valparaiso. Kaylon Williams and Ryan Allen added 12 points for Milwaukee. The Panthers were 14 of 24 from 3-point range, with Haarsma making three and Williams two from that range. Milwaukee led by as many as 26 points. Ray McCallum led the Titans (9-11, 3-5) with 23 points. Chase Simon scored 14 points and Eli Holman had 12 points and 11 rebounds for Detroit.
